      "why_people_believe_it": "People find this claim compelling because it offers a simple explanation for a complex issue and taps into the fear of harming one's child, which is an emotional response that can be hard to ignore.",
      "counter_narrative": "Imagine the relief of protecting your child from preventable diseases with vaccines.",
      "origin_hypothesis": "The claim that 'vaccines cause autism' originated from a 1998 paper published in The Lancet by Andrew Wakefield, which was later retracted due to serious procedural errors and ethical violations.",
      "timeline_summary": "The claim that vaccines cause autism originated from a retracted paper by Andrew Wakefield in 1998, which gained significant media attention and sparked an anti-vaccine movement. The Lancet retracted the paper in 2010 due to ethical violations. Major health organizations have since debunked the claim, emphasizing that extensive research shows no link between vaccines and autism."
    },
